1
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:02,666
the first two things we will want to automate are

2
00:00:02,666 --> 00:00:04,133
silicon and plastic

3
00:00:04,533 --> 00:00:07,400
we can start with the more streamlined one silicon

4
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:10,400
which can easily be produced with a simple chain of machines

5
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:11,900
with no input at all

6
00:00:12,233 --> 00:00:14,633
the first part of this chain is rather easy

7
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:17,100
so we can just skip to the last step

8
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:18,833
the issue with that step is that

9
00:00:18,833 --> 00:00:21,333
an addition of magnesium is required

10
00:00:21,633 --> 00:00:23,700
it will be given back in form of magnesia

11
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:25,900
which has to be sorted out from silicon

12
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:28,333
and electrolyzed to get magnesium back

13
00:00:28,466 --> 00:00:29,833
to sort apart those items

14
00:00:29,833 --> 00:00:31,400
we can use drawers or barrels

15
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:33,833
and lock the item we want to sort out

16
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:37,233
once we have isolated the dust we wanted to reprocess

17
00:00:37,233 --> 00:00:40,466
we can use conveyor to import it inside our electrolyzer

18
00:00:40,733 --> 00:00:44,233
with that we have finished the logistic part of producing silicon

19
00:00:44,466 --> 00:00:46,400
now let's see the power part

20
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:48,800
the main power sink here is the arc furnace

21
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:51,066
with its 3 amps of MV power

22
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:54,066
however that consumption will last just 1 second

23
00:00:54,066 --> 00:00:55,700
and will yield the two outputs

24
00:00:55,900 --> 00:00:57,633
this will cause an interesting effect 

25
00:00:57,633 --> 00:01:00,200
which we'll be using but I do not advise

26
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,833
when a machine runs out of power

27
00:01:01,833 --> 00:01:03,266
it will halt for a little bit

28
00:01:03,266 --> 00:01:06,300
and fill up its internal buffer before trying again

29
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:10,533
and this recipe is quick enough to be run even without a proper power source

30
00:01:10,566 --> 00:01:13,200
furthermore, this machine is not going to work constantly

31
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:16,500
but it's going to have to wait for the slower ones in this chain

32
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:20,866
which means it's going to use a constant average of 32 EU per tick

33
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,866
that doesn't mean it can be powered with LV power

34
00:01:23,866 --> 00:01:28,600
but it allows us to power everything in this chain with just a single MV turbine

35
00:01:28,933 --> 00:01:31,500
finally we add two more chemical reactors

36
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:34,033
to refine our silicon to solar grade

37
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:36,400
next we have to make polyethylene

38
00:01:36,466 --> 00:01:39,233
the main issue here is deciding in which way

39
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:42,100
we can either set up a new farm for the plant way

40
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:44,500
or set up a pump and refine some oil

41
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:47,200
the plant way is more renewable

42
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:49,500
but oil is more synthetically interesting

43
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:51,633
so we will be seeing the oil way

44
00:01:52,033 --> 00:01:54,266
after setting up a pump over a deposit

45
00:01:54,266 --> 00:01:58,000
we move the oil to our base using a long distance fluid pipeline

46
00:01:58,433 --> 00:02:01,100
the first step will be to distill our oil

47
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:06,233
and here we'll already start to get lost between all of the recipes in the distillery page

48
00:02:06,233 --> 00:02:11,333
a better way to deal with all of those recipes is to instead look at the distillation tower recipes

49
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:13,666
while we can't craft that machine yet

50
00:02:13,666 --> 00:02:16,300
the outputs are in most of the cases the same

51
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:21,866
the circuit required in the distillery represents the layer at which the fluid will come out of the tower

52
00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:27,033
and yes by using a single block we will be losing all of the fluids outside of the chosen one

53
00:02:27,133 --> 00:02:30,233
the issue is now deciding which fluid we want to keep

54
00:02:30,500 --> 00:02:32,500
and things quickly get convoluted

55
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:40,233
because to make plastic each one of those fluids can be working a slightly different way to get different ratios in a second distillation process

56
00:02:40,433 --> 00:02:43,200
anyways we start by moving the oil into a distillery

57
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:45,100
and then we select one fluid

58
00:02:45,266 --> 00:02:47,333
this fluid will have some sulfur impurities

59
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:51,300
which must be removed with the help of some hydrogen in a chemical reactor

60
00:02:51,466 --> 00:02:55,600
the main issue here is that one of the two fluids must be provided through cells

61
00:02:55,666 --> 00:02:58,700
to help with that we can use some GregTech tanks

62
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:01,000
we pump in the fluid, add some cells

63
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,100
and then apply a conveyor belt to move the filled cells

64
00:03:04,133 --> 00:03:07,900

this particular recipe will output two differently filled cells


65
00:03:07,933 --> 00:03:10,466
for now we have to either manually manage those

66
00:03:10,466 --> 00:03:11,900
or use the drawer trick

67
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:14,333
the next step is similar, but easier to loop

68
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:18,000
since it consists of just moving back and forth a cell to refill it

69
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:18,733
as before

70
00:03:18,733 --> 00:03:20,600
we will have a tank to refill the cells

71
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:24,633
which are then pushed into the adjacent chemical reactor with a conveyor belt

72
00:03:24,633 --> 00:03:25,600
but this time

73
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:29,700
we will also have a conveyor on the reactor to push back empty cells

74
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:32,333
however those conveyors will block each other

75
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:35,133
unless we select the allow input setting

76
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:38,300
and with that we have severely cracked refinery gas

77
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:41,900
one of the 12 different routes of making ethylene from oil

78
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:45,466
finally we add oxygen to obtain polyethylene

79
00:03:45,633 --> 00:03:47,800
this process uses a little bit of hydrogen

80
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,400
and a huge amount of oxygen

81
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:52,000
to get the hydrogen we are electrolyzing water

82
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,266
and while this process makes some oxygen too

83
00:03:54,266 --> 00:03:56,266
it's far from our requirements

84
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:58,333
the easiest way to make all of that oxygen

85
00:03:58,333 --> 00:04:01,733
is to just use the waste one from our silicon processing

86
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:05,600
one other thing you could want to automate is ore processing

87
00:04:06,066 --> 00:04:07,733
here we have an example of that

88
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:10,200
made using steam and logistic pipes

89
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,066
let's see how it works

90
00:04:12,133 --> 00:04:15,033
in this test we drop all of the minerals we dig

91
00:04:15,433 --> 00:04:17,433
if those are already sorted out

92
00:04:17,433 --> 00:04:21,433
they will be moved to the machine we have designed for the next processing step

93
00:04:21,733 --> 00:04:22,633
in this example

94
00:04:22,633 --> 00:04:25,933
we are setting the destination filters with item sink modules

95
00:04:25,933 --> 00:04:30,433
and extracting materials from the outputs with unfiltered extractor modules

96
00:04:30,533 --> 00:04:32,666
every time we will be inserting a new ore

97
00:04:32,666 --> 00:04:34,366
it will stick in the starting chest

98
00:04:34,366 --> 00:04:37,833
that will be the signal that we have to decide how to process it

99
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:41,300
to do that we can use NEI bookmarks to Mark the path we decide

100
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:45,100
then we apply those bookmarks to the cards of the correct machines

101
00:04:45,100 --> 00:04:47,700
another thing is that until we get into HV

102
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:51,233
we can't get the useful byproduct of the HV macerator

103
00:04:51,266 --> 00:04:54,200
so we should be careful of what we process until then

104
00:04:54,433 --> 00:04:55,500
on the opposite side

105
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:59,800
sometimes some useless byproduct processing is going to clog things up

106
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:02,100
to speed up things and save some energy

107
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:04,200
we can use some different machines

108
00:05:04,433 --> 00:05:06,666
to finish off, I'd like to remind you that

109
00:05:06,666 --> 00:05:14,300
you can quickly restrict flow direction of a long segment of pipes by setting the wrench in line mode by crouching and clicking on air

110
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:16,400
and for today that's it

111
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:17,000
bye bye

112
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:02,666
我们想要自动化的前两件事是

113
00:00:02,666 --> 00:00:04,133
硅粉和塑料

114
00:00:04,533 --> 00:00:07,400
我们可以从更线性的硅粉开始

115
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:10,400
它可以很容易地用简单的机器链生产

116
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:11,900
而几乎不需要输入

117
00:00:12,233 --> 00:00:14,633
这条链的第一部分相当简单

118
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:17,100
所以我们可以跳到最后一步

119
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:18,833
这一步的问题是

120
00:00:18,833 --> 00:00:21,333
需要额外添加镁

121
00:00:21,633 --> 00:00:23,700
它将以氧化镁的形式返还

122
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:25,900
我们需要把它产物从硅中分离出来

123
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:28,333
并电解以取回镁

124
00:00:28,466 --> 00:00:29,833
要分类产物

125
00:00:29,833 --> 00:00:31,400
我们可以用抽屉或桶

126
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:33,833
并锁定我们要整理的物品

127
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:37,233
一旦我们分离了想要重新处理的粉

128
00:00:37,233 --> 00:00:40,466
我们可以使用传送带将其导入电解机内

129
00:00:40,733 --> 00:00:44,233
这样我们就完成了生产硅粉的物流部分

130
00:00:44,466 --> 00:00:46,400
现在让我们看看电力部分

131
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:48,800
这里的主要用电器是电弧炉

132
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:51,066
它要用 3A MV

133
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:54,066
然而，耗电仅持续1秒

134
00:00:54,066 --> 00:00:55,700
并将产生两个输出

135
00:00:55,900 --> 00:00:57,633
这会引起有趣的效果

136
00:00:57,633 --> 00:01:00,200
我们将使用它，但我不建议这样做

137
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,833
当机器没电时

138
00:01:01,833 --> 00:01:03,266
它会停一会儿

139
00:01:03,266 --> 00:01:06,300
并在再次尝试之前填满其内部缓冲区

140
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:10,533
这个配方足够快，即使没有合适的电源也能运行

141
00:01:10,566 --> 00:01:13,200
此外，这台机器不会一直工作

142
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:16,500
因为它必须等待这个链条中较慢的那些

143
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:20,866
这意味着它平均来说，将使用 32 EU/t

144
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,866
这并不意味着它可以用LV电源供电。

145
00:01:23,866 --> 00:01:28,600
但它允许我们用一个MV涡轮机
为这个产线中的所有东西供电

146
00:01:28,933 --> 00:01:31,500
最后我们再加两个化学反应釜

147
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:34,033
将我们的硅提炼成太阳能级硅

148
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:36,400
接下来我们要做聚乙烯

149
00:01:36,466 --> 00:01:39,233
这里的主要问题是决定以哪种方式生产

150
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:42,100
我们可以建立一个新的农场，用植物来生产

151
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:44,500
或者建立一个泵并提炼石油

152
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:47,200
植物方式更具可再生性

153
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:49,500
但是石油综合来说更有趣

154
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:51,633
所以我们会看到石油产线

155
00:01:52,033 --> 00:01:54,266
在油泉上安装泵后

156
00:01:54,266 --> 00:01:58,000
我们用长距离输油管道把石油运到基地

157
00:01:58,433 --> 00:02:01,100
第一步是提炼石油

158
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:06,233
在这里，我们已经在蒸馏页面的所有配方之间晕头转向了

159
00:02:06,233 --> 00:02:11,333
处理所有这些配方的更好方法是查看蒸馏塔配方

160
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:13,666
虽然我们还不能制造那台机器

161
00:02:13,666 --> 00:02:16,300
在大多数情况下，输出是相同的

162
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:21,866
小蒸馏所需的电路代表了蒸馏塔的流体产出层

163
00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:27,033
是的，通过使用单方块
我们将失去所选层之外的所有液体

164
00:02:27,133 --> 00:02:30,233
现在的问题是决定我们要保留哪种液体

165
00:02:30,500 --> 00:02:32,500
事情很快就会变得复杂

166
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:40,233
因为要制造塑料，每种液体都可以以稍微不同的方式
在第二道蒸馏工序中获得不同的产率

167
00:02:40,433 --> 00:02:43,200
不管怎样，我们从把石油搬进小蒸馏开始

168
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:45,100
然后我们选择一种流体

169
00:02:45,266 --> 00:02:47,333
这种液体会有一些硫杂质

170
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:51,300
必须在化学反应釜中借助氢移除

171
00:02:51,466 --> 00:02:55,600
这里的主要问题是两种液体中的一种必须通过单元提供

172
00:02:55,666 --> 00:02:58,700
为了解决这个问题，我们可以使用GT缸

173
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:01,000
我们注入液体，加入一些空单元

174
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,100
然后使用传送带移动填满的单元

175
00:03:04,133 --> 00:03:07,900

此特定配方将输出两个不同填充的单元


176
00:03:07,933 --> 00:03:10,466
现在我们要么手动管理这些

177
00:03:10,466 --> 00:03:11,900
或者使用抽屉技巧

178
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:14,333
下一步类似，但更容易循环

179
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:18,000
因为它只包括来回移动一个单元来重新填充它

180
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:18,733
和以前一样

181
00:03:18,733 --> 00:03:20,600
我们用一个缸来装满单元

182
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:24,633
然后用传送带将其输入相邻的化学反应器

183
00:03:24,633 --> 00:03:25,600
但这一次

184
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:29,700
我们还将在反应釜上安装传送带，将空单元推回

185
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:32,333
然而，这些传送带会相互阻挡

186
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:35,133
除非我们选择允许输入

187
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:38,300
这样我们就有了重度裂化的炼油气

188
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:41,900
石油制乙烯的12种不同方法之一

189
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:45,466
最后我们加入氧气得到聚乙烯

190
00:03:45,633 --> 00:03:47,800
这个过程需要一点氢气

191
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,400
和大量的氧气

192
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:52,000
为了得到氢，我们电解水

193
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,266
虽然这个过程也会产生一些氧气

194
00:03:54,266 --> 00:03:56,266
这与我们的要求相差甚远

195
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:58,333
制造所有氧气的最简单方法

196
00:03:58,333 --> 00:04:01,733
就是用我们硅加工的废料

197
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:05,600
你可能想要自动化的另一件事是矿石处理

198
00:04:06,066 --> 00:04:07,733
这里我们有一个例子

199
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:10,200
使用蒸汽和物流管道制造

200
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,066
让我们看看它是如何工作的

201
00:04:12,133 --> 00:04:15,033
在这个测试中，我们放入挖掘的所有矿物

202
00:04:15,433 --> 00:04:17,433
如果这些已经被标记过了

203
00:04:17,433 --> 00:04:21,433
它们将被转移到我们为下一步加工设计的机器上

204
00:04:21,733 --> 00:04:22,633
在这个例子中

205
00:04:22,633 --> 00:04:25,933
我们正在使用物品收纳模块设置目标过滤器

206
00:04:25,933 --> 00:04:30,433
并使用未经过滤的提取模块从输出中提取材料

207
00:04:30,533 --> 00:04:32,666
每次我们都会放入新矿石

208
00:04:32,666 --> 00:04:34,366
它会一直呆在初始箱子里

209
00:04:34,366 --> 00:04:37,833
这将是我们必须决定如何处理它的信号

210
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:41,300
为此，我们可以使用NEI书签来标记我们决定的路径

211
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:45,100
然后我们将这些书签应用到正确机器的模块上

212
00:04:45,100 --> 00:04:47,700
另一件事是在我们进入HV之前

213
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:51,233
我们无法得到HV研磨机的有用副产品

214
00:04:51,266 --> 00:04:54,200
所以在那之前我们应该注意我们处理的东西

215
00:04:54,433 --> 00:04:55,500
在另一边

216
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:59,800
有时一些无用的副产品加工会堵塞东西

217
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:02,100
为了加快速度并节省一些电量

218
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:04,200
我们可以使用一些不同的机器

219
00:05:04,433 --> 00:05:06,666
最后，我想提醒你

220
00:05:06,666 --> 00:05:14,300
你可以通过蹲下并单击空气将扳手设置为直线模式
来快速限制长管道的流动方向

221
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:16,400
今天就这样了

222
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:17,000
拜拜

